&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE POSITION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Playworks Michigan, we are focused on delivering high-quality, consistent programming that supports students and the adults who serve them every day. We are seeking a motivated team member to support program delivery, coach school staff, and help create engaging play environments across partner sites. This is a hands-on role for someone who is organized, reliable, and committed to delivering high-quality work. This role is responsible for executing Playworks’ program model with consistency and quality across assigned partner schools, under the leadership of the Associate Program Director.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Site Coordinator, you will support implementation of Playworks programming through coaching, modeling, and collaboration with school staff. You will work directly with school administration, teachers, and recess teams to apply Playworks strategies and systems that support a positive and engaging play environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CORE FOCUS OF THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and support the delivery of Playworks’ consultative, play-based program model across 2–4 assigned partner schools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver coaching, modeling, and consultation to school personnel aligned with Playworks practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure consistent implementation of program components aligned to regional expectations and standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support school staff in applying Playworks strategies across settings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to a strong, consistent partner experience through reliable program delivery and responsive school-partnership support.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with school administration, educators, and recess teams to schedule program delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver on-site coaching, consultation, and modeling to school personnel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support implementation of core program components, including recess, student leadership (Junior Coach program), and instructional classes (Class Game Time)&lt;/li&gt;
